title: H.S. boys soccer: Fort Lee passes on appeal
text:
H.S. boys soccer: Fort Lee passes on appeal October 13, 2015 Last updated: Tuesday, October 13, 2015, 1:21 AM The Record Print 
Fort Lee will not appeal its loss to Don Bosco on Sunday in the Bergen County boys soccer tournament after all. 
On Monday, Fort Lee athletic director Michael Raftery said that an eligibility issue involving a Don Bosco player was resolved following the Ironmen's 4-3 win in a penalty-kick shootout in the round of 16 game. 
The player in question is eligible. 
Fort Lee will not take any action to contest the game despite its coach, Demba Mane, saying Sunday that he would file an appeal. 
Don Bosco (7-4) – which has won 11 Bergen championships, more than any school in the 44-year history of the event – will take on fourth-seeded Ramapo in the quarterfinals Sunday.
